  <text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
    <body>
      <div xml:id="Aink0">
        <lg type="edition">
          <l> nīla mēṉi vāliḻai pākat</l>
          <l> toruva ṉirutā ṇiḻaṟkīḻ</l>
          <l> mūvakai yulaku mukiḻttaṉa muṟaiyē.</l>
        </lg>
        <lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
          <l> All three kinds of world budded in the [proper] manner/in order </l>
          <p/>
          <l rend="indent4"> under the shade of the two feet of one man, </l>
          <p/>
          <l> (1) who has as a half [the woman with] pure jewels, and who has a blue form i.e. throat
            (Šiva and Parvatī)/ </l>
            <p/>
          <l> (2) who has a share [reserved] on his blue body for [the woman who is] a pure jewel (Viṣṇu
            and Lakṣmī). </l>


        </lg>
      </div>
    </body>
